Popular Lagos-based cleric Kingsley Okonkwo has advised singles on the need to build relationships on a foundation that is lasting PK, as he’s also called, said most singles find it unbelievable that relationships void of s3x actually exists in today’s world. He argued such perception is faulty adding, he has wedded more virgins than non-virgins. According to the lead pastor and founder of David’s Christian Center in a sermon titled: “It’s possible to have a s3xually pure relationship”, until one meets their spouse and eventually tie the knot, every s3xual experience(s) gathered prior to that time is a total waste. The relationship coach/counsellor said: “Most people believe that in the day and age. Is it possible to have a relationship without s3x? The answer is capital YES!   Anambra: Appeal Court to hear APC, Andy Uba’s appeal…     Modu-Sheriff: I don’t want to be President but APC chairman     Vermaelen retires, sets to become Belgian assistant coach   - Advertisement - “It’s possible to have a relationship where there’s no sex. Don’t let any devil deceive you. “Don’t go and build a relationship on a foundation that will never stand. There are many godly relationships. “I have had more virgins wedded than non-virgins in my life. They have a chance for their marriage lasting than all these experiences you’re gathering. “Until you meet the person you want to marry any experience you’re gathering is a waste of time.” “Some of you, you’ve done over syllabus. You have PHD in sexology. The person you want to marry is OND or school cert (WAEC).”